You scored as Buddhism. Your beliefs most closely resemble those of Buddhism. Do more research on Buddhism and possibly consider becoming Buddhist, if you are not already. In Buddhism, there are Four Noble Truths: (1) Life is suffering. (2) All suffering is caused by ignorance of the nature of reality and the craving, attachment, and grasping that result from such ignorance. (3) Suffering can be ended by overcoming ignorance and attachment. (4) The path to the suppression of suffering is the Noble Eightfold Path, which consists of right views, right intention, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right-mindedness, and right contemplation. These eight are usually divided into three categories that base the Buddhist faith: morality, wisdom, and samadhi, or concentration. In Buddhism, there is no hierarchy, nor caste system; the Buddha taught that one's spiritual worth is not based on birth.

Ok... so Im the only person I know who even realizes the Genius of Zero Mostel... if orgasms were based upon comedy... He would be a SEX GOD!!!  True... his characters tend to be... rather schauvantistic... but hey... he's still awesome... Ben thinks Im crazy, but I find a movie about a slave in ancient Rome, who tricks his master into setting him free, and gets a free concubine out of the deal (who happens to be silent) extremely funny... Of course... we can't forget this movie <A funny thing happened on the way to the forum> contains other great comedians... Im not sure of all their names... mostly they are old slapstick comedians... including BUSTER KEATON!!! Anyways... I sooooo need to find a poster of Zero Mostel... he may be an ugly old guy with a mop over... but hey... he's hysterical... If I had to chose whom I wished to meet between him, and the sexiest man on earth, I would oh so pick Zero... 

Ok... now that everyone thinks there is something seriously wrong with me... I will go on with why my title talks about only the greatest musical ever... Fiddler on the Roof (well... actually this, and A funny thing happened on the way to the forum as well.)  I, for the most part, despise musicals... as in... I got my mother to let me go home sick during the two days that we had to watch "the west side story" in class... and I still got an A on the paper I wrote about it... anyways... Musicals bother me... they tend to have little plot... or they are some stupid sloppy romance and it's all complete bullshit... well... Fiddler was one of only two musicals I ever watched, where I felt there was more to it than the music.  I literally fell in love with this musical.  I've only ever seen the film version... Zero Mostel originally played Tevye but in the film version they casted Topol who was kick ass... 

Anyways... I could go on all night about my favorite movies... but as most people look at me as if Im insane (either because they haven't heard of them... or else they hate them) I think I will start a random tangent. 

Friends... I was thinking today that I have good friends... and I do... but sometimes I fear if they knew everything I thought, or did, they would run shrieking from the room.  It's not that Im so different I suppose... or really that strange... I just view things differently...  For instance... my best friend in Chapel Hill pokes fun at me for my slight obsession with blood.  It stemmed out of an old relationship and the fact that I used to cut myself.  anyways... he tells me Im "all into violence, you dirty, dirty girl"... which really isn't the case... because I don't like to inflict pain on people... and I don't like people to inflict pain on me... I do seem to like hurting myself sometimes... though I refrain from it... it has too many times led me down the path of suicide attempts... but, Im not about to tell him this.  He jokes Im into S&M but... in reality... I could care less about that stuff... 

The other problem with friends is that I am extremely jealous... not of them... but more of the fact that they have other friends... which is completely rediculous... I know they love me... and I love them... but the truth of the matter is, I am extremely jealous when they have other friends... though, strangely enough, if Im friends with their other friends, I don't have a problem with it.  Only the ones that I either dislike, or do not know.  I try my best not to show them, because it wouldn't be fair on them.  It isn't that I do not want them to have friends... it mainly that I fear that those friends will replace me... and then they will forget all about me... and I'll be left alone.  Strangely, this is my largest fear.  I love being alone sometimes... in fact... I have to be alone for some portion of the day or else I go insane... and when I mean portion of the day, I mean 2 or 3 hrs at the least.  but the thought of having to be alone makes my chest seize up and causes me to want to scream.  

Anyways... I think that's it for tonight... Im exhausted.... *hugs*...

hmm... I've been thinking and I realized something.  I suck.  Well... actually I just realized that I will do nothing important with my life.  My mother wants me to become a rich Doctor and do marvelous things.  I have no interest in this... but far be it from me to not do what someone wants me to do.  I think I'd really like to study religion and become a Professor or even perhaps a priest(however unlikely it may be).  I could just see my mother's reaction... if she didn't disown me, she would talk about me as if I were the black sheep.  She already does this to some extent... I am the slacker... the child who "has it all" and is wasting it... uhm... yes... Lets just say... at 7 I was listening to this stuff... and it hasn't stopped yet.  
So what am I to do... my father says, "do what you like", but... he doesn't understand how very scary my mother can be... she scares me still... Im 19 and I still want to run and hide whenever she is even slightly angry.  More than that, sometimes I want to run her through with a knife 500 times until she realizes how much I dislike her.  I won't say hate... I don't hate her... I love her a lot... and while it may be sick and twisted, my life has been so far dedicated to getting her to like me.  But I dont understand what is so bad about me all the time.  I mean sure... Im not perfect, but she makes it out like I've put her through hell and back.  No one really understands she and I.  Ben, my best friend, hates her guts and thinks she's horrid.  My father says she's mentally ill and too afraid to face that.  Everyone else I know remains silent, or backs her up.  And me?... Outwardly I bash her... and inwardly I wonder why I am so awful that she wishes I was never born.  
Anyways... the original point of this entry was to talk about my future... oh I hate waiting.  I want to know what will happen.  I swear, sometimes I think it would be easier to drop out and become homeless, and in some ways it would.  I would become so occupied with staying warm, and fed that I would lose sight of these other problems.  But... I must admit, I dont think I could do it.  1. I like being clean, and having nice showers.  2.  I like food... lol
Anyways... I dont know what I'll end up doing, but whatever it is, it will never measure up to peoples expectations... I suppose I should do something that makes me happy... but... unfortunately... I dont know if I can do that... *sighs* 

Oh, Dear Lord in heaven... my mood icon looks like it's on crack... hahahahahahhahahahahahahahahahaha!!!!!!!!!!!!!

SO... Im hating myself and everyone else right now... I have a big test, a quiz and surveys to give out all by tomorrow.  *Im a slight procrastinator*... but be that as it may, I still feel bad.  I swear if I get through tomorrow, Im going to celebrate by getting coldstone!!! 

Anyways... enough of that stuff... Im looking for a job... I hate hunting for a job... People cant tell you, "we're not hiring"... so you fill out the damned application, only to find out that they wont be reviewing it until the moon crashes into the earth, and the sun explodes... *hates job hunting with a passion*... but I do need money, so I must do it.  I mean... I found a job all the other times I've looked, so why not now?... ahh well.. Ill think about it more tommarow... 

Finnally... Ben tried to get me drunk last night... we had tequila *nasty stuff*... unfortunately I didnt get drunk... sure I got slightly tipsy... but it lasted all of 20 minutes... We had a nalgene bottle about 2/3 full of tequilla... Ben probably had about half of that... and I had about a third of that... Ben was pretty drunk... while I was... annoyed... anyways... it was an interesting saturday night...

So... Im at home.  I am home for fall break, and lets just say my mother and I are already not at ease with each other.  Today my mother told me that she didnt think I should come home for thanksgiving, because she had things to do that weekend and the week after and it would be too stressful.  (what's stressful about having your husband come pick up your daughter and bring her home... and have her sleep on the couch and stay out of your way?).  Im starting to think my mother gets some kind of sick pleasure from causing me pain.  (she's an emotional sadist)... She likes to push my buttons and push me over the edge of sanity.  But then she has to take it a step further by saying mean things... I mean... there is no rationale to them and I really shouldn't be offended, but who likes to have their mother essentially tell them that they're worthless and no one wants them around.  My mother told me when I was 7 that she didnt want me and that I was an accident because her Birth control stopped working.  She told me this until I was 15.  Thats when I asked my father about it and he said my mother lied.  But why would my mother tell me that?  I mean... she and my father were trying to have children when they had me, so why would my mother tell me I was the biggest mistake she ever made?... who knows... I suppose I better go.  ahh... *prays that the rest of fall break will be better*

Yes... I watched them... Quite interesting actually... Finally they got off the topic of War in Iraq and War on terrorism, and got into some domestic  topics... Thank God... I'm sick of hearing about Iraq and Terrorism, I want to hear about things like health care, social security, reducing the national debt, creating jobs, and Taxes.  I eagerly await the third debate where they will supposedly focus solely on domestic topics and the economy.

Ok... so my long thumbs say HEY YA'll!!! anyways... yeah... so I am ready to give up on some stuff.  Ever noticed that sometimes people just dont get the subtleties.  ARGH!!! It makes me want to scream... but who knows... 

Ben, one of me bestest friends, has been having some interesting relationship problems... of course... I have relationship problems... or rather problem... the problem... (doesnt have a relationship).  

Apparently Ben thinks I give really good, motivating advice.  (apparently Im the white oprah<- straight from Ben's mouth)... this is really funny because of how cynical and sarcastic I am concerning myself... 

anyways... I dont know the point of this journal... mainly Im just frustrated with life... WHEE!!!

Ok... Im sick... Im sick of it all... I give up... I wonder if I just disappeared if anyone would care... I doubt it... I should just go away... leave people alone... then maybe they and I would be happier... who knows... I give up... I really wish something would just happen... so that I could disappear... It would make it easier... I think Ill just go...

So... my father works as a lawyer for legal aid in north carolina.  and I am the volunteer receptionist... aka... I am that cheerful person that people get angry at.  But that's ok... I talked to this lovely lady today.  She was 82, though she didnt seem like it.  She and I talked about Bush, and the election, and politics.  Lauren often doesnt discuss these things with people outside of her family, because she lives in the buckle of the bible belt... aka everyone is conservative (for the most part), right winged, and republican... Not too mention, there are many crazy southern baptists... trust me... Im related to some... they are CRAZY!!!! and Lauren being the flaming liberal democrat that she is, doesnt wish to get attacked... but this Lady was a very liberal, and very active democrat.  She and I became good friends in the two hours that we talked while she waited on her friend.  She was quite interesting, had seen Fahrenheit 9/11, and has been the highlight of my day so far... I think if it gets any better, Ill die.  lol... 

anyways... other than that, Ive been answering phones, turned down a twenty dollar tip for finding a number for a man, and have joked around with Celia, Lisa, and Shelly.  I need to call psychiatrists, but I havent had a chance... maybe during my lunch hour... ahh well... this is all for now

Ok... so... I think I may have mentioned my cat Rumpole... But this journal entry isnt about him... its about the person he's named after.  He's named after a character from a book and movie series.  This Character, Horas Rumpole, is an English Barrister (lawyer) at the Old Bailey.  He is a constant defender... never prosecuting... always defending those of the criminal class... its actually very funny... and the Character, Rumpole, is quite witty, sarcastic and dramatic.  He's surrounded by a load of other characters (mostly lawyers or Solicitors *people who give assign cases*).  These characters include the married and extremely promiscuous Claude Erskin Brown, the stupid, religiously devout and "forward" thinking Sam Ballard.  Then of course there is his Wife, Hilda, who is known as "She who must be obeyed".  Needless to say, she's rather forceful and orders poor Rumpole around.  There are also many other characters, but if I were to list them all, I would never finish... Anyways... I bring this up because I am currently watching a Rumpole episode... Anyways... yes... this is who my cat was named after... 

Other than this... there is nothing interesting going on.  Im sitting here, eating pizza, watching Rumpole, and listening to my mother bitch to my grandmother on the phone.  No... not bitch at, just complain about stuff... I dont know how my grandmother deals with it... too much of it, your eyes glaze over, and you start to foam at the mouth.  

Well... anyways... Im bored... I might have more to write later.. ta ta...
